This paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance on classification tasks, specifically in terms of accuracy, robustness, and efficiency. The paper proposes a new solution called Robust Dynamic Inference Networks (RDI-Nets) that allows for input-adaptive inference, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance on classification tasks. The paper also discusses adversarial attacks and defenses, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new solution that optimizes model efficiency, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
